args:
When a mysterious life form emerges from the
gate, Ilia uses alchemy to give it humanoid
flesh and names it Mordecai. Zethia and a
faerie named Meene are confused, but Ilia
declares Mordecai her greatest creation.
Still, we've got to look alive; Augus and\nhis goons could come along any minute.
We should put some distance\nbetween us and them.
Yeah, probably my lab blowing up.\nGuessing the mana kiln went haywire.

Probably couldn't withstand the power of
the opposing poles. Better throw that on
the giant pile of improvements to make
whenever I get a spare minute... Hrm...
Right! Bad guys chasing us. Sorry, I tend\nto get distracted when science comes up.\nBack to running!
Please, hold a moment. I realize how late\nin the day it is for introductions, but...\nWho are you?
Oh, right. Haven't introduced myself yet.\nI'm Ilia.
Oh, er...it's nothing. My name is Zethia.
Sorry for putting you in all that danger,\nZethia. Totally my bad.
I want to explain the situation, so I'd like\nyou to come with me—AND you!
I'm sorry, but who is the second ＂you＂\nin that sentence?
It came from the gate I opened earlier.\nGuess it's following us for some reason.

I couldn't stand having something I brought
from another world being put to ill use,
so better bring it along.
...Let's go, you!
We'll head over to my hideout.
A woman with the same name as the\nGoddess in a world of a thousand years\nago... Whatever is happening here?
Did you take a detour?\nI was so worried!
You're still going to be overprotective\nwhen I'm an old lady, aren't you?\nOh, and I brought a couple guests.
Ilia made a friend? Oh, how delightful!\nBut yes, hello. I am Ilia's foster mother.\nYou may call me Meene.
Hmm? Your mana...\nAre you a spiritual projection?!
(It's true: My body is being used as a\nvessel for the Other in my own world.)
Crafting a body out of mana is difficult\neven for us faeries. However did you\nmanage to do it?
Questions can wait, Meene!\nYou have another guest to greet.
Ilia! Did you open a gate?!
Look at the big brain on Mom!
Humanity is ALREADY in conflict\nwith the dragons, Ilia.
Yet you would have us keep here an\notherworldly being that they so detest?\nPlease send it back at once.
Aw, it's fine. I'm going to look after it.
This is no pet, Ilia! I swear, sometimes I\nthink you enjoy making me worry over you.

And I swear you would wrap me in a
blanket and never let me leave the house
if you had your way!
...C'mere little fella.
*sigh* Where did I go wrong with you?
Forgive me for showing up uninvited.
Oh, it's all right. I've learned to expect\nsuch things from my Ilia.
Now have a seat while I prepare some\nspecialty faerie herbal tea.
(Such beautiful wings! While much larger\nthan Notte, she's still clearly a faerie.)
(But what am I supposed to do now?)
Hey, so where's your body? And how DID\nyou know about gates, anyway?
Ilia, you mustn't pry into people's affairs\nlike that. It is terrifically rude.
Yes, Mom. But okay, if you're not\nthe chatty type, I guess I'll have\nto do the talking.
I'm being pursued by the government\nbecause they want my research.
Exactly. They want to summon a creature\nfrom the otherworld so they can turn it into\na weapon of war. ...So typical.
Anyway, they'll do anything they can to get\nwhat they want—including killing people.
I'm sorry you ended up involved with that\nmess today, because it means they've\nnow set their sights on you, too.
Probably best to lie low and stay away\nfrom the city for a while.
Oh, looks like it's done!\nExcuse me a minute.
(She appears to be making something.\nSome kind of baked good, perhaps?)
*sigh* I hope whatever she's making is\nnothing dangerous, but I've also learned\nbetter than to hold such hopes tightly.
It's truly beautiful—my greatest work ever.\nWell? What do you think, Zethia?
I'm sorry, what is this?\nIt looks almost like...
Wait, hold on. You seriously don't know\nwhat alchemy is?! SERIOUSLY?!
(If I'm not mistaken, this era was the\ngolden era of alchemy. Perhaps such\nthings are perfectly normal here.)
N-not at all! I was merely a bit surprised.
Hmm... Well, anyway, this is a little\nphysical form I made for that light\nwe brought here.
When it followed me, I realized it\nseemed to have a will of its own.
So I wondered if maybe we could\ncommunicate and come to understand\neach other if it had a physical body.
Oh come now, this is simply too much!\nYou're giving a body to a being from\nthe otherworld!
I TOLD you I'd look after it! Sheesh.\nSo what's your name, new friend?
Don't know, huh? Okay then,\nI'll give you one.
(It looks similar to Morsayati, but I don't\nsense any malice or evil from it.)
(Has my meeting with Ilia here caused a\nchange in history?)
(If Ilia didn't bump into me, would she\nhave escaped those soldiers and been\nable to complete her research?)
(If history has indeed been changed,\nthen what will become of the future?)
